<a id="AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback"></a>

# AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback

**Inherits:** [AudioStreamPlaybackResampled](AudioStreamPlaybackResampled.md) **\<** [AudioStreamPlayback](AudioStreamPlayback.md) **\<** [RefCounted](RefCounted.md) **\<** [Object](Object.md)

Plays back audio generated using [AudioStreamGenerator](AudioStreamGenerator.md).

<!-- classref-introduction-group -->

## Description

This class is meant to be used with [AudioStreamGenerator](AudioStreamGenerator.md) to play back the generated audio in real-time.

<!-- classref-introduction-group -->

## Tutorials

- [Audio Generator Demo](https://godotengine.org/asset-library/asset/2759)

- [Godot 3.2 will get new audio features](https://godotengine.org/article/godot-32-will-get-new-audio-features)

## Method Descriptions

<a id="AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback_method_can_push_buffer"></a>

<!-- classref-method -->

[bool](bool.md) **can_push_buffer**\ (\ amount\: [int](int.md)\ ) <span class="const">const</span> [ðŸ”—](#AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback_method_can_push_buffer)

Returns ``true`` if a buffer of the size `amount` can be pushed to the audio sample data buffer without overflowing it, ``false`` otherwise.

<hr class="classref-item-separator"/>

<a id="AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback_method_clear_buffer"></a>

<!-- classref-method -->

`void` **clear_buffer**\ (\ ) [ðŸ”—](#AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback_method_clear_buffer)

Clears the audio sample data buffer.

<hr class="classref-item-separator"/>

<a id="AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback_method_get_frames_available"></a>

<!-- classref-method -->

[int](int.md) **get_frames_available**\ (\ ) <span class="const">const</span> [ðŸ”—](#AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback_method_get_frames_available)

Returns the number of frames that can be pushed to the audio sample data buffer without overflowing it. If the result is ``0``, the buffer is full.

<hr class="classref-item-separator"/>

<a id="AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback_method_get_skips"></a>

<!-- classref-method -->

[int](int.md) **get_skips**\ (\ ) <span class="const">const</span> [ðŸ”—](#AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback_method_get_skips)

Returns the number of times the playback skipped due to a buffer underrun in the audio sample data. This value is reset at the start of the playback.

<hr class="classref-item-separator"/>

<a id="AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback_method_push_buffer"></a>

<!-- classref-method -->

[bool](bool.md) **push_buffer**\ (\ frames\: [PackedVector2Array](PackedVector2Array.md)\ ) [ðŸ”—](#AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback_method_push_buffer)

Pushes several audio data frames to the buffer. This is usually more efficient than [push_frame()](AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback.md#AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback_method_push_frame) in C# and compiled languages via GDExtension, but [push_buffer()](AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback.md#AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback_method_push_buffer) may be *less* efficient in GDScript.

<hr class="classref-item-separator"/>

<a id="AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback_method_push_frame"></a>

<!-- classref-method -->

[bool](bool.md) **push_frame**\ (\ frame\: [Vector2](Vector2.md)\ ) [ðŸ”—](#AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback_method_push_frame)

Pushes a single audio data frame to the buffer. This is usually less efficient than [push_buffer()](AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback.md#AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback_method_push_buffer) in C# and compiled languages via GDExtension, but [push_frame()](AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback.md#AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback_method_push_frame) may be *more* efficient in GDScript.
